author: Adam Voge
title: Hornig expands Uptown Minneapolis empire
text:
Home / News / Real Estate / Hornig expands Uptown Minneapolis empire The 50-unit Calhoun Beach Apartments, at 2905 E. Dean Parkway in Minneapolis, were constructed in 1926. The fully leased building, which is now owned by Hornig Cos., is just north of Lake Calhoun. (Staff photo: Bill Klotz) Hornig expands Uptown Minneapolis empire By: Adam Voge July 9, 2015 3:58 pm 0 Hornig Cos. beat out a dozen bidders for a seven-building, 192-unit portfolio of brownstone apartments.
